elements.title: Dudleya cymosa subsp. pumila
elements.contents: ... that the Sonoran blue butterfly uses Dudleya cymosa subsp. pumila (pictured) as a larval foodplant and hummingbirds feed on its nectar?

elements.title: Twin Parks
elements.contents: ... that the Twin Parks housing project in New York City, the site of a January 2022 fire that killed seventeen people, won architectural awards after it was constructed in the early 1970s?

elements.title: Jeffrey Rosenfeld
elements.contents: ... that Australian neurosurgeon Jeffrey Rosenfeld led the team developing a wireless device that promises to give limited vision to the totally blind?

elements.title: Little Theatre
elements.contents: ... that the Little Theatre, once deemed a "gem among playhouses", was later planned to be replaced by a driveway for The New York Times?

elements.title: Ioan Caragea
elements.contents: ... that the 1810s reign of Ioan Caragea introduced Wallachia to carom billiards, sugar sculptures, and an eponymous plague?

elements.title: La Poutine Week
elements.contents: ... that La Poutine Week is the world's largest poutine festival, with 700 restaurants serving 350,000 people?

elements.title: Rod Beaton
elements.contents: ... that while waiting for an interview, journalist Rod Beaton was involved in a shoving incident with baseball player Barry Bonds?

elements.title: Godzilla Megamullion
